# HEUREKA UI Recreation Plan

## Goal Description
Recreate the HEUREKA landing page and authentication paths based on the provided Replit site. The app is a modern real estate SaaS and needs a very clean, dynamic user interface crafted with Vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. We will use plain HTML files and vanilla CSS to avoid reliance on Node.js/build tools. The app will include three main pages: [index.html](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/index.html), [login.html](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/login.html), and [register.html](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/register.html).

## Proposed Changes
### Project Setup
- Create base HTML structure and styling folder.
- Establish shared [styles.css](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/styles.css).

### Base Files
#### [NEW] [styles.css](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/styles.css)
Contains root color variables, reset, font imports, layout classes, button utilities, and form styles.
- Primary color: Navy Blue (`#0a192f`).
- Typography: Inter font imported from Google Fonts.

### Pages
#### [NEW] [index.html](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/index.html)
The main landing page featuring:
- Hero section with badge and CTAs
- Responsive navigation bar
- Features grid

#### [NEW] [login.html](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/login.html)
Authentication page featuring a split-screen design.

#### [NEW] [register.html](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/register.html)
Registration page maintaining layout parity with login.

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
- Open HTML pages sequentially in the browser.
- Review aesthetics across the Home, Login, and Register pages.
- Verify micro-interactions: Hover states on buttons, smooth scrolling if applicable.

