# Phase 2: Town Hall RAG & Conformity
## Goal Description
Enable municipalities to upload their official PLU documents (Knowledge Base), and force the Conformity AI to use these specific uploaded documents as the source of truth when analyzing citizens' CERFA requests.

## Proposed Architecture
### 1. Database (`db/src/schema/`)
#### [NEW] `townHallDocuments.ts`
- Create `townHallDocumentsTable` to store metadata and raw text of uploaded PLU documents for a specific municipality.
- Fields: `id`, `municipalityId`, `title`, `fileName`, `rawText`, `createdAt`.

### 2. Backend API ([api-server/src/routes/mairie.ts](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/Web-SaaS-Builder/artifacts/api-server/src/routes/mairie.ts) & [pluAnalysis.ts](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/Web-SaaS-Builder/artifacts/api-server/src/services/pluAnalysis.ts))
#### [MODIFY] [mairie.ts](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/Web-SaaS-Builder/artifacts/api-server/src/routes/mairie.ts)
- Add `POST /api/mairie/documents` to accept PDF uploads (using `multer` + `pdf-parse`).
- Add `GET /api/mairie/documents` to list uploaded PLU files.
- Add `DELETE /api/mairie/documents/:id` to manage the knowledge base.

#### [MODIFY] AI Conformity Engine
- Update the CERFA analysis pipeline: instead of relying on the general Geoportail API or general knowledge, the system will inject the concatenated `rawText` of all uploaded `townHallDocuments` into the `gpt-4o-mini` prompt as the absolute source of truth for checking conformity.

### 3. Frontend UI ([heureka/src/pages/portail-mairie.tsx](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/Web-SaaS-Builder/artifacts/heureka/src/pages/portail-mairie.tsx))
#### [MODIFY] [portail-mairie.tsx](file:///Users/evideletang/Desktop/HEUREKA/Web-SaaS-Builder/artifacts/heureka/src/pages/portail-mairie.tsx)
- Add a tabs architecture: "Dossiers CERFA" (current view) vs "Base de Connaissance PLU" (new view).
- In the "Base de Connaissance" tab, build a drag-and-drop file uploader.
- Display a list/table of active PLU documents currently defining the AI's knowledge base.

## Verification Plan
1. Log in as a `mairie` user.
2. Upload 2 mock PLU PDFs to the Knowledge Base.
3. Submit a dummy CERFA document via the user portal.
4. Verify the backend logs to ensure the AI uses the uploaded PDFs text to grade the CERFA conformity.
